    "narrative": "The **Kyle Tucker** (74.43) and **Drake Baldwin** (70.94) tandem headline our lineup today, representing the elite tier of our projections. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a high-floor matchup against Dustin May, bolstered by favorable wind conditions that provide a modest boost to his power potential. **Drake Baldwin**, currently slotted for a #2 order role, is the primary beneficiary of a positive park factor and a manageable matchup against Kyle Freeland, solidifying his role as our offensive anchor. **Josh Lowe** (65.17) also merits attention; despite the threat of a high-efficiency opponent, his dynamic platoon advantage against Clay Holmes makes him a high-leverage start, particularly as we look to capitalize on his speed-centric profile in this Roto environment.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the staff was the exclusion of **Coby Mayo** (52.34), who nearly cracked the lineup over **Dominic Smith** (49.69). While **Coby Mayo** possesses a superior offensive upside, the optimizer leaned toward the specific platoon and park factors surrounding **Dominic Smith** in the high-scoring environment of his matchup. We also kept **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (51.19) on the bench today, as the matchup against Ryan\u2019s xERA of 3.39 suppressed his efficiency score just enough to keep him out of the starting slots. \n\nRisk management remains paramount, as our entire lineup is subject to the \"Lineup Pending\" designation. We are tracking the weather closely for wind-impacted games, particularly for **Gunnar Henderson** (55.35), whose score is suppressed by a difficult assignment against Max Fried. While **Gunnar Henderson** remains in the lineup due to his irreplaceable status, the \"Elite Hold\" capability of his opponent necessitates careful monitoring of his stolen base opportunities throughout the game. All owners should verify official lineups at the 30-minute pre-game window to ensure that secondary options like **Heliot Ramos** are ready to rotate in should the assumed batting orders shift unfavorably.",
